# Ola CRM frontend — Vite build-time env
# Copy to `frontend/.env.local` (gitignored) for per-machine overrides.
# `frontend/.env` is committed and holds shared defaults for all dev machines.

# Backend host the dev server should hit (Vite proxies /api and /export here).
# Default = local backend on port 8888. Override only when pointing at a remote backend.
VITE_BACKEND_SERVER="http://localhost:8888/"

# UI-only dev mode: short-circuit the login wall and stub all axios calls
# with mock responses (see frontend/src/request/devMockInterceptor.js).
# Use case: wzh works on UI/styles without needing a running backend.
#
# Notes:
#   - Only active when `npm run dev` (Vite dev mode). `npm run build` (prod)
#     tree-shakes the entire mock module via `import.meta.env.DEV` — the
#     interceptor file is not bundled into the prod artifact.
#   - Leave unset (or `false`) for normal full-stack dev against a real backend.
# VITE_DEV_BYPASS_AUTH=true
